<br>
I was awarded a Khalshazar last week.  I am currently using Khal mainhand, Wicked Shank offhand.  I put the 125dd Ruj augment on Khal so I am very happy with its dps in mainhand for now, not to mention the extra benefit of the - agro proc.  I have been coveting emp sword and more recently, Agnarr sword for offhand.  My guild is almost flagged for Sol Ro Tower and will be working on RZ and Sol Ro shortly.  <br>
<br>
My question is whether or not you think I should just hold off on weapons until Gold Runed Mithril Knife then mainhand GRMK and offhand Khal.  Or should I take my chances with trying to get emp sword or agnarr sword and go from there.<br>
<br>
I am kind of leaning towards waiting for GRMK because I have a few other armor slots that could use upgrading.  I have my eye set on Earing of Falling Stars and Talisman of V.K. for upgrades in the future.  If you have a sec, take a peek at my magelo and let me know what you think.  Thanks.<br>
<br>
This post is also meant to jumpstart this forum!<br>
<br>
